              <li><strong>Element:</strong> Use <code>&lt;input type="range"&gt;</code> for native keyboard and screen reader support.</li>
              <li><strong>Label association:</strong> Connect <code>&lt;label for="id"&gt;</code> to the <code>&lt;input id="id"&gt;</code>.</li>
              <li><strong>Range type:</strong> Use two <code>&lt;input type="range"&gt;</code> elements; associate with <code>aria-labelledby</code> and communicate min/max of each thumb via <code>aria-valuemin</code>, <code>aria-valuemax</code>, <code>aria-valuenow</code>.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider"/>

          <div class="doc-section">
            <h3 id="aria-attributes-screen-reader-guidance" class="doc-h3">ARIA Attributes &amp; Screen Reader Guidance</h3>
            <ul class="doc-list">
              <li><strong>aria-valuenow:</strong> Set on the input to reflect the current value.</li>
              <li><strong>aria-valuemin / aria-valuemax:</strong> Set the valid range boundaries on the input.</li>
              <li><strong>aria-valuetext:</strong> Use for non-numeric displays (e.g. "Low", "Medium", "High").</li>
              <li><strong>aria-describedby:</strong> Associate error/helper text with the input for screen readers.</li>
              <li><strong>aria-invalid:</strong> Set to <code>"true"</code> on the input when in Error state.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider"/>

          <div class="doc-section">
            <h3 id="focus-state-design" class="doc-h3">Focus State Design</h3>
            <ul class="doc-list">
              <li><strong>Focus ring:</strong> Uses <code>Border/Border-Accent-Focus</code> &mdash; must remain visible. Do not suppress <code>:focus-visible</code> outline.</li>
              <li><strong>Focus ring size:</strong> Matches thumb container per size (24 / 28 / 32 px), stroke 2 px.</li>
              <li><strong>Step markers:</strong> If shown, mark the track with <code>aria-label</code> or visually-hidden text describing the step values.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider"/>

          <div class="doc-section">
            <h3 id="disabled-state" class="doc-h3">Disabled State</h3>
            <ul class="doc-list">
              <li>Set <code>disabled</code> on <code>&lt;input type="range"&gt;</code>. Disabled sliders are removed from the tab order.</li>
              <li>All elements (track, thumb, labels) are greyed out using disabled tokens.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider"/>

          <div class="doc-section">
